{
  "stem": "2391.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The whole thing was a nightmare, absolute nightmare.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And she also says people had changed dramatically.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Everybody was scared.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Everybody was afraid.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They would walk-- they were afraid to talk.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Every time they would say a word that was not considered 100%, they would always look around to make sure nobody was following them, nobody was listening, nobody was spying.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They-- everybody felt persecuted.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But that's-- that's what the government wanted them to feel like, you know?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They, they were holding them through fear to do-- to, to doing what they wanted them to do.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Fear was a great weapon.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And when your mother went back and she stayed with her family, these were not German Jews, were they, that she stayed with at that time?",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, it was her family.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were-- they were non-Jews.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Her family was in danger too, because they came many times, you know, to their place and, and, and checking them out.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And asking what happened, what-- how can you explain, you know, the fact that your daughter married a Jew and this sort of thing.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they got a lot of-- they got a lot of abuse and insults as a result, too, constantly.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They, they also had to cope with a lot.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And luckily, nobody got, got arrested from her immediate family.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Luckily.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But it was very-- and they made sure that life was going to be very unpleasant for them as a result, because they considered, you know, everybody marrying a Jew as some kind of a traitor or whatever.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I don't know what they called them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was a horrible thing in their eyes to do.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Strangely enough, I don't know of many cases their-- where the wife divorced the husband or vice versa as a result.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
